node.text:
Kai Alexander
Born May 28,2021 at 4:18 am 
7lbs 6 oz 

Here are some moments of his first 48 hours. Motherhood is the best feeling I have ever experienced. Although it has been a hard few days, postpartum depression is no joke! Countless days of no sleep and worry for your baby, motherhood is definitely exhausting. But I love every moment of it. I am slowly learning that it is okay and there is no such thing as a perfect mother. 

I love being your mother. My blood, sweat, and tears are all worth it at the end just to make sure you are alright. Mommy and daddy are doing this all for you baby Kai. 💙
.
📸: @clairehesser
.
.
.
.
.
